<subSubSection id="C37E65015A7E980AFF54F37BEF4EF238" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A7E980AFF54F37BEF4EF238" blockId="9.[160,1365,2934,3477]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis id="B910EA985A7E980AFF54F37BEC0EF354" bold="true" box="[163,523,3288,3321]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Critically Endangered on The IUCN Red List. De Winton’s Golden Mole is known from only one location and has not been caught for 50 years. It is no doubt severely threatened by habitat alteration resulting from alluvial diamond mining and infrastructure resulting from expansion of Port Nolloth harbor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
